    How to fix?
  </h2> <div class="vue--prose" data-v-6b6ff1c7 data-v-8ae1d1c4><div class="vue--markdown-to-html markdown-description" data-v-185c2450 data-v-8ae1d1c4><p>Upgrade <code>github.com/mattermost/mattermost-server/v6/api4</code> to version 6.0.3 or higher.</p>
</div></div> </div></div></div> <div data-v-43af9ae8 data-v-194b7320><div class="markdown-section" data-v-8ae1d1c4 data-v-194b7320><h2 class="vue--heading heading" data-v-8dd2f746 data-v-8ae1d1c4>
    Overview
  </h2> <div class="vue--prose" data-v-6b6ff1c7 data-v-8ae1d1c4><div class="vue--markdown-to-html markdown-description" data-v-185c2450 data-v-8ae1d1c4><p><a href="https://mattermost.org">github.com/mattermost/mattermost-server/v6/api4</a> is an open source, private cloud, Slack-alternative from <a href="https://mattermost.org">https://mattermost.org</a>.</p>
<p>Affected versions of this package are vulnerable to Denial of Service (DoS) due to improper sanitization of user's password in audit logs when user creation fails.</p>
</div></div> </div></div><div data-v-43af9ae8 data-v-194b7320><div class="markdown-section" data-v-8ae1d1c4 data-v-194b7320><h2 class="vue--heading heading" data-v-8dd2f746 data-v-8ae1d1c4>
    Details
  </h2> <div class="vue--prose" data-v-6b6ff1c7 data-v-8ae1d1c4><div class="vue--markdown-to-html markdown-description" data-v-185c2450 data-v-8ae1d1c4><p>Denial of Service (DoS) describes a family of attacks, all aimed at making a system inaccessible to its intended and legitimate users.</p>
<p>Unlike other vulnerabilities, DoS attacks usually do not aim at breaching security. Rather, they are focused on making websites and services unavailable to genuine users resulting in downtime.</p>
<p>One popular Denial of Service vulnerability is DDoS (a Distributed Denial of Service), an attack that attempts to clog network pipes to the system by generating a large volume of traffic from many machines.</p>
<p>When it comes to open source libraries, DoS vulnerabilities allow attackers to trigger such a crash or crippling of the service by using a flaw either in the application code or from the use of open source libraries.</p>
<p>Two common types of DoS vulnerabilities:</p>
<ul>
<li><p>High CPU/Memory Consumption- An attacker sending crafted requests that could cause the system to take a disproportionate amount of time to process. For example, <a href="SNYK-JAVA-COMMONSFILEUPLOAD-30082">commons-fileupload:commons-fileupload</a>.</p>
</li>
<li><p>Crash - An attacker sending crafted requests that could cause the system to crash. For Example,  <a href="https://snyk.io/vuln/npm:ws:20171108">npm <code>ws</code> package</a></p>
</li>
</ul>
</div></div> </div></div><div data-v-43af9ae8 data-v-194b7320><div class="markdown-section" data-v-8ae1d1c4 data-v-194b7320><h2 class="vue--heading heading" data-v-8dd2f746 data-v-8ae1d1c4>

    How to fix?
  </h2> <div class="vue--prose" data-v-6b6ff1c7 data-v-8ae1d1c4><div class="vue--markdown-to-html markdown-description" data-v-185c2450 data-v-8ae1d1c4><p>Upgrade <code>github.com/mattermost/mattermost-server/v6/api4</code> to version 0.6.1 or higher.</p>
</div></div> </div></div></div> <div data-v-43af9ae8 data-v-194b7320><div class="markdown-section" data-v-8ae1d1c4 data-v-194b7320><h2 class="vue--heading heading" data-v-8dd2f746 data-v-8ae1d1c4>
    Overview
  </h2> <div class="vue--prose" data-v-6b6ff1c7 data-v-8ae1d1c4><div class="vue--markdown-to-html markdown-description" data-v-185c2450 data-v-8ae1d1c4><p><a href="https://mattermost.org">github.com/mattermost/mattermost-server/v6/api4</a> is an open source, private cloud, Slack-alternative from <a href="https://mattermost.org">https://mattermost.org</a>.</p>
<p>Affected versions of this package are vulnerable to Denial of Service (DoS) by posting a crafted message with a modified <code>deleted_at</code> JSON parameter.</p>
</div></div> </div></div><div data-v-43af9ae8 data-v-194b7320><div class="markdown-section" data-v-8ae1d1c4 data-v-194b7320><h2 class="vue--heading heading" data-v-8dd2f746 data-v-8ae1d1c4>
    Details
  </h2> <div class="vue--prose" data-v-6b6ff1c7 data-v-8ae1d1c4><div class="vue--markdown-to-html markdown-description" data-v-185c2450 data-v-8ae1d1c4><p>Denial of Service (DoS) describes a family of attacks, all aimed at making a system inaccessible to its intended and legitimate users.</p>
<p>Unlike other vulnerabilities, DoS attacks usually do not aim at breaching security. Rather, they are focused on making websites and services unavailable to genuine users resulting in downtime.</p>
<p>One popular Denial of Service vulnerability is DDoS (a Distributed Denial of Service), an attack that attempts to clog network pipes to the system by generating a large volume of traffic from many machines.</p>
<p>When it comes to open source libraries, DoS vulnerabilities allow attackers to trigger such a crash or crippling of the service by using a flaw either in the application code or from the use of open source libraries.</p>
<p>Two common types of DoS vulnerabilities:</p>
<ul>
<li><p>High CPU/Memory Consumption- An attacker sending crafted requests that could cause the system to take a disproportionate amount of time to process. For example, <a href="SNYK-JAVA-COMMONSFILEUPLOAD-30082">commons-fileupload:commons-fileupload</a>.</p>
</li>
<li><p>Crash - An attacker sending crafted requests that could cause the system to crash. For Example,  <a href="https://snyk.io/vuln/npm:ws:20171108">npm <code>ws</code> package</a></p>
</li>
</ul>
</div></div> </div></div><div data-v-43af9ae8 data-v-194b7320><div class="markdown-section" data-v-8ae1d1c4 data-v-194b7320><h2 class="vue--heading heading" data-v-8dd2f746 data-v-8ae1d1c4>

  </h2> <div class="vue--prose" data-v-6b6ff1c7 data-v-8ae1d1c4><div class="vue--markdown-to-html markdown-description" data-v-185c2450 data-v-8ae1d1c4><p><a href="https://mattermost.org">github.com/mattermost/mattermost-server/v6/api4</a> is an open source, private cloud, Slack-alternative from <a href="https://mattermost.org">https://mattermost.org</a>.</p>

    How to fix?
  </h2> <div class="vue--prose" data-v-6b6ff1c7 data-v-8ae1d1c4><div class="vue--markdown-to-html markdown-description" data-v-185c2450 data-v-8ae1d1c4><p>Upgrade <code>github.com/mattermost/mattermost-server/v6/api4</code> to version 5.37.7, 6.1.2, 6.2.2, 6.3.1 or higher.</p>
</div></div> </div></div></div> <div data-v-43af9ae8 data-v-194b7320><div class="markdown-section" data-v-8ae1d1c4 data-v-194b7320><h2 class="vue--heading heading" data-v-8dd2f746 data-v-8ae1d1c4>
    Overview
  </h2> <div class="vue--prose" data-v-6b6ff1c7 data-v-8ae1d1c4><div class="vue--markdown-to-html markdown-description" data-v-185c2450 data-v-8ae1d1c4><p><a href="https://mattermost.org">github.com/mattermost/mattermost-server/v6/api4</a> is an open source, private cloud, Slack-alternative from <a href="https://mattermost.org">https://mattermost.org</a>.</p>
<p>Affected versions of this package are vulnerable to Informarion Exposure via the <code>api4/team.go</code> component, which leaks the team leader's information.</p>
</div></div> </div></div><div data-v-43af9ae8 data-v-194b7320><div class="markdown-section" data-v-8ae1d1c4 data-v-194b7320><h2 class="vue--heading heading" data-v-8dd2f746 data-v-8ae1d1c4>
    Details
  </h2> <div class="vue--prose" data-v-6b6ff1c7 data-v-8ae1d1c4><div class="vue--markdown-to-html markdown-description" data-v-185c2450 data-v-8ae1d1c4><p>Denial of Service (DoS) describes a family of attacks, all aimed at making a system inaccessible to its intended and legitimate users.</p>
<p>Unlike other vulnerabilities, DoS attacks usually do not aim at breaching security. Rather, they are focused on making websites and services unavailable to genuine users resulting in downtime.</p>
<p>One popular Denial of Service vulnerability is DDoS (a Distributed Denial of Service), an attack that attempts to clog network pipes to the system by generating a large volume of traffic from many machines.</p>
<p>When it comes to open source libraries, DoS vulnerabilities allow attackers to trigger such a crash or crippling of the service by using a flaw either in the application code or from the use of open source libraries.</p>
<p>Two common types of DoS vulnerabilities:</p>
<ul>
<li><p>High CPU/Memory Consumption- An attacker sending crafted requests that could cause the system to take a disproportionate amount of time to process. For example, <a href="SNYK-JAVA-COMMONSFILEUPLOAD-30082">commons-fileupload:commons-fileupload</a>.</p>
</li>
<li><p>Crash - An attacker sending crafted requests that could cause the system to crash. For Example,  <a href="https://snyk.io/vuln/npm:ws:20171108">npm <code>ws</code> package</a></p>
</li>
</ul>
</div></div> </div></div><div data-v-43af9ae8 data-v-194b7320><div class="markdown-section" data-v-8ae1d1c4 data-v-194b7320><h2 class="vue--heading heading" data-v-8dd2f746 data-v-8ae1d1c4>

Rather, they are focused on making websites and services unavailable to genuine users resulting in downtime.\n\nOne popular Denial of Service vulnerability is DDoS (a Distributed Denial of Service), an attack that attempts to clog network pipes to the system by generating a large volume of traffic from many machines.\n\nWhen it comes to open source libraries, DoS vulnerabilities allow attackers to trigger such a crash or crippling of the service by using a flaw either in the application code or from the use of open source libraries.\n\nTwo common types of DoS vulnerabilities:\n\n* High CPU\u002FMemory Consumption- An attacker sending crafted requests that could cause the system to take a disproportionate amount of time to process.
